  "abstract": "The production of multivariate time-series data facilitates the continuous monitoring of production assets. The modelling approach of multivariate time series can reveal the ways in which parameters evolve as well as the influences amongst themselves. These data can be used in tandem with artificial intelligence methods to create insight on the condition of production equipment, hence potentially increasing the sustainability of existing manufacturing and production systems, by optimizing resource utilization, waste, and production downtime. In this context, a predictive maintenance method is proposed based on the combination of LSTM-Autoencoders and a Transformer encoder in order to enable the forecasting of asset failures through spatial and temporal time series. These neural networks are implemented into a software prototype. The dataset used for training and testing the models is derived from a metal processing industry case study. Ultimately, the goal is to train a remaining useful life (RUL) estimation model.",
